cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper deals with natural language inference (NLI) and improving model robustness through adversarial datasets. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses machine learning techniques and generalization, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions numerical reasoning and syntactic complexity, which could relate to cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), respectively.
